00:08:52.100 --> 00:08:56.090 align:middle line:84%
And he also said, it's
up to us as humanity

00:08:56.090 --> 00:08:57.080 align:middle line:90%
for that to succeed.

00:08:57.080 --> 00:08:58.790 align:middle line:84%
It's not the Earth
or self doing,

00:08:58.790 --> 00:09:00.722 align:middle line:84%
it's us being here in
relationship with Earth.

00:09:00.722 --> 00:09:01.805 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: She's already--

00:09:01.805 --> 00:09:02.540 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: She's doing it.

00:09:02.540 --> 00:09:03.457 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --doing it.

00:09:03.457 --> 00:09:05.840 align:middle line:84%
It's up to us to come into
resonance with the Earth

00:09:05.840 --> 00:09:08.270 align:middle line:90%
and what she already gives us.

00:09:08.270 --> 00:09:09.800 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:11.660 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't agree more.

00:09:11.660 --> 00:09:18.620 align:middle line:84%
And once I read an esoteric
document by Saint John

00:09:18.620 --> 00:09:21.230 align:middle line:84%
on the subject of
armageddon that

00:09:21.230 --> 00:09:27.960 align:middle line:84%
was at once terrifying in its
description, and so beautiful

00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:30.230 align:middle line:84%
in the elevation of
what it was saying

00:09:30.230 --> 00:09:34.400 align:middle line:84%
happens at that time, what
happens in this transition time

00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:35.390 align:middle line:90%
by way of love.

00:09:35.390 --> 00:09:39.680 align:middle line:84%
And it's all love that fuels
where we go as a species.

00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:44.480 align:middle line:84%
And so brilliant,
brilliant being.

00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:47.520 align:middle line:84%
So now in your own background,
just a little bit before we

00:09:47.520 --> 00:09:49.520 align:middle line:84%
go into some of the people
because we've already

00:09:49.520 --> 00:09:52.280 align:middle line:84%
told people we're going to talk
about some of the scientists

00:09:52.280 --> 00:09:54.680 align:middle line:84%
and what they came across
in their own lives.

00:09:54.680 --> 00:09:58.350 align:middle line:84%
You worked with Deepak
Chopra for quite a long time.

00:09:58.350 --> 00:10:02.600 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about how your
relationship-- what you learned

00:10:02.600 --> 00:10:04.790 align:middle line:84%
in your relationship with
Deepak and why you were

00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:06.110 align:middle line:90%
drawn to do that to begin with?

00:10:06.110 --> 00:10:06.910 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Yeah.

00:10:06.910 --> 00:10:09.500 align:middle line:84%
Meeting Deepak was very, very
helpful for me, my career.

00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:12.620 align:middle line:84%
In fact, meeting
him was the reason

00:10:12.620 --> 00:10:17.810 align:middle line:84%
I could eventually start tapping
into consciousness studies.

00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:20.105 align:middle line:84%
He and I had a meeting,
a chance meeting

00:10:20.105 --> 00:10:21.230 align:middle line:90%
at a scientific conference.

00:10:21.230 --> 00:10:23.450 align:middle line:84%
We started speaking about
integrative medicine which

00:10:23.450 --> 00:10:26.300 align:middle line:84%
is an area I was doing
research in at the time.

00:10:26.300 --> 00:10:29.390 align:middle line:84%
We both started lamenting
that integrative medicine

00:10:29.390 --> 00:10:30.830 align:middle line:84%
and integrative
medicine research

00:10:30.830 --> 00:10:32.690 align:middle line:84%
is not at all
really integrative.

00:10:32.690 --> 00:10:35.690 align:middle line:84%
The vision is for that,
but it's still fragmented.

00:10:35.690 --> 00:10:39.050 align:middle line:84%
It's still reductionistic
as is the biomedical model.

00:10:39.050 --> 00:10:41.030 align:middle line:84%
So we decided we
needed to conduct

00:10:41.030 --> 00:10:43.190 align:middle line:84%
research that was
truly integrative,

00:10:43.190 --> 00:10:44.780 align:middle line:90%
whole person, which we did.

00:10:44.780 --> 00:10:46.400 align:middle line:84%
We designed a
beautiful study called

00:10:46.400 --> 00:10:49.610 align:middle line:84%
the self-directed biological
transformation initiative,

00:10:49.610 --> 00:10:51.860 align:middle line:84%
which was on a whole
person medical system,

00:10:51.860 --> 00:10:54.090 align:middle line:90%
ayurveda in this case.

00:10:54.090 --> 00:10:56.070 align:middle line:84%
Ayurveda, as you know,
in Tibetan medicine,

00:10:56.070 --> 00:10:58.680 align:middle line:84%
all the traditional
systems understand

00:10:58.680 --> 00:11:00.840 align:middle line:84%
the transcendental nature
of the human being,

00:11:00.840 --> 00:11:02.320 align:middle line:90%
consciousness itself.

00:11:02.320 --> 00:11:04.830 align:middle line:84%
So doing that research
study and others we did

00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:08.280 align:middle line:84%
led me naturally to begin
to discuss the transcendent

00:11:08.280 --> 00:11:12.780 align:middle line:84%
in the context of our scientific
publications, journals,

00:11:12.780 --> 00:11:14.280 align:middle line:90%
talks at conferences.

00:11:14.280 --> 00:11:16.800 align:middle line:84%
And that led me to
say, I just need

00:11:16.800 --> 00:11:20.070 align:middle line:84%
to start speaking about this,
my own personal experience,

00:11:20.070 --> 00:11:23.430 align:middle line:84%
I'll highlight other scientists
who have had such experiences,

00:11:23.430 --> 00:11:26.590 align:middle line:84%
and who have been in
the closet, so to speak.

00:11:26.590 --> 00:11:28.860 align:middle line:84%
And this gets back to
the vision of love.

00:11:28.860 --> 00:11:31.570 align:middle line:84%
The question is, what has
science been doing for us?

00:11:31.570 --> 00:11:33.840 align:middle line:84%
And honestly, as you know,
it's been a hindrance.

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:34.710 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It has
been a hindrance.

00:11:34.710 --> 00:11:35.670 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Most people--

00:11:35.670 --> 00:11:37.920 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It ridicules
those who speak that way.

00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:39.200 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Yeah.

00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:41.540 align:middle line:84%
Most people look to
science for answers,

00:11:41.540 --> 00:11:43.460 align:middle line:84%
and we have Western
science, particularly

00:11:43.460 --> 00:11:45.170 align:middle line:84%
materialism aspect,
who basically

00:11:45.170 --> 00:11:48.380 align:middle line:84%
say there's no mystical,
there's no metaphysical.

00:11:48.380 --> 00:11:51.690 align:middle line:84%
So people then believe that and
say, OK, well, there isn't any.

00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:52.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm just going to--

00:11:52.490 --> 00:11:53.660 align:middle line:90%
I'll do something else here.

00:11:53.660 --> 00:11:56.030 align:middle line:84%
I'll follow some
other trajectory

00:11:56.030 --> 00:11:57.890 align:middle line:84%
and I won't have
the encouragement

00:11:57.890 --> 00:11:59.880 align:middle line:90%
to develop it myself.

00:11:59.880 --> 00:12:01.040 align:middle line:90%
So it's been an impediment.

00:12:01.040 --> 00:12:05.210 align:middle line:84%
I want to see science evolve
out of materialism just

00:12:05.210 --> 00:12:08.000 align:middle line:84%
like we as human beings need
to evolve out of our egotism

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:11.160 align:middle line:84%
to get us to the next step.
if science does that, great.

00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:13.370 align:middle line:84%
If it doesn't please
get out of the way.

00:12:13.370 --> 00:12:14.870 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah,
get out of the way.

00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:17.630 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: And let's unfold
this as we need it to be,

00:12:17.630 --> 00:12:19.020 align:middle line:90%
and now is the time.

00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:19.820 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It is.

00:12:19.820 --> 00:12:24.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, to me, we're at such
a kind of critical juncture

00:12:24.920 --> 00:12:31.010 align:middle line:84%
in this, as you say, ability to
understand, feel, and propagate

00:12:31.010 --> 00:12:33.290 align:middle line:84%
love in all its
forms in the most

00:12:33.290 --> 00:12:34.940 align:middle line:90%
simple and sweetest levels.

00:12:34.940 --> 00:12:37.700 align:middle line:84%
People think, oh my
god, how are we going

00:12:37.700 --> 00:12:39.350 align:middle line:90%
to have a planet based on love?

00:12:39.350 --> 00:12:41.415 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I was
meditating recently--

00:12:41.415 --> 00:12:43.040 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't meditating,
I was sitting down

00:12:43.040 --> 00:12:45.060 align:middle line:84%
to read a book and
all of a sudden,

00:12:45.060 --> 00:12:46.590 align:middle line:84%
I got that funny
feeling, I thought,

00:12:46.590 --> 00:12:49.100 align:middle line:84%
oops, there's someone
who wants to talk to me.

00:12:49.100 --> 00:12:51.950 align:middle line:84%
So I closed my eyes and I
actually got my cell phone

00:12:51.950 --> 00:12:53.810 align:middle line:84%
and thought, it feels
like something I

00:12:53.810 --> 00:12:55.708 align:middle line:90%
need to probably write down.

00:12:55.708 --> 00:12:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And so I just recorded
it on my cell phone.

00:12:57.500 --> 00:13:00.830 align:middle line:84%
And it turned out it was
really an ode to love,

00:13:00.830 --> 00:13:02.990 align:middle line:84%
and every way in
which people can love.

00:13:02.990 --> 00:13:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And that this whole notion of
bringing love onto this planet

00:13:07.850 --> 00:13:11.220 align:middle line:90%
is not a heroic effort at all.

00:13:11.220 --> 00:13:15.470 align:middle line:84%
It's just taking a
moment to feel uplifted,

00:13:15.470 --> 00:13:19.700 align:middle line:84%
to feel an appreciation
for another person,

00:13:19.700 --> 00:13:23.930 align:middle line:84%
for a little pet, for
nature, for a piece of music.

00:13:23.930 --> 00:13:27.060 align:middle line:84%
All of that is a
reflection of love.

00:13:27.060 --> 00:13:29.630 align:middle line:84%
And if every person would
give themselves permission

00:13:29.630 --> 00:13:32.780 align:middle line:84%
and understand the
necessity and maybe really

00:13:32.780 --> 00:13:37.340 align:middle line:84%
the directive for us to take
those moments and feel this,

00:13:37.340 --> 00:13:39.260 align:middle line:90%
it starts.

00:13:39.260 --> 00:13:40.457 align:middle line:90%
It just starts.

00:13:40.457 --> 00:13:42.290 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: It does because
it's all in there.

00:13:42.290 --> 00:13:45.050 align:middle line:84%
You just need permission
and somewhat of a setting.

00:13:45.050 --> 00:13:45.860 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:13:45.860 --> 00:13:46.850 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: And then it begins.

00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:48.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It does,
and it starts in mass.

00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:52.490 align:middle line:84%
The more people that can
embrace simple, simple practices

00:13:52.490 --> 00:13:56.030 align:middle line:84%
like this, like gratitude, which
is just love and appreciation,

00:13:56.030 --> 00:13:57.710 align:middle line:90%
it's just love.

00:13:57.710 --> 00:14:00.610 align:middle line:84%
I think that's why people like
gratitude meditation so much.

00:14:00.610 --> 00:14:01.610 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: It's powerful.

00:14:01.610 --> 00:14:02.430 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It's very powerful.

00:14:02.430 --> 00:14:04.730 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: It overcomes
duality and separation.

00:14:04.730 --> 00:14:06.020 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It really does.

00:14:06.020 --> 00:14:09.500 align:middle line:84%
So now when we're getting
down to these scientists,

00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:15.000 align:middle line:84%
their spirit and their mind,
and how do they work with that?

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:17.780 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: So most of the
scientists I interviewed had--

00:14:17.780 --> 00:14:20.960 align:middle line:84%
well, some had a kind of
a transpersonal spiritual

00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:23.630 align:middle line:84%
awakening while they
were already scientists,

00:14:23.630 --> 00:14:25.130 align:middle line:84%
and I'll mention
one now in terms

00:14:25.130 --> 00:14:27.920 align:middle line:84%
of gratitude and compassion
since we were just

00:14:27.920 --> 00:14:29.000 align:middle line:90%
speaking about that.

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:33.920 align:middle line:84%
Some had more psychic spiritual
capabilities as young children,

00:14:33.920 --> 00:14:35.840 align:middle line:84%
and that led them to
become scientists.

00:14:35.840 --> 00:14:37.440 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Right,
to figure out why.

00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:38.240 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:40.240 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: So one of the
scientists, for example,

00:14:40.240 --> 00:14:42.110 align:middle line:84%
her name is Professor
Dusana Dorjee.

00:14:42.110 --> 00:14:43.543 align:middle line:90%
She's out of York University.

00:14:43.543 --> 00:14:44.960 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah,
I like her story.

00:14:44.960 --> 00:14:46.430 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: And she was--

00:14:46.430 --> 00:14:47.360 align:middle line:90%
it's a great story.

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:50.090 align:middle line:84%
She was deep into Buddhist
meditation, compassion

00:14:50.090 --> 00:14:52.940 align:middle line:84%
meditation, gratitude
meditation, and that

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:55.130 align:middle line:84%
led her eventually
into what's often

00:14:55.130 --> 00:14:57.800 align:middle line:84%
called a non-dual state,
non-duality, non-dual

00:14:57.800 --> 00:15:00.320 align:middle line:90%
awareness, essentially oneness.

00:15:00.320 --> 00:15:02.150 align:middle line:84%
That can be a challenging
state for people

00:15:02.150 --> 00:15:04.160 align:middle line:84%
to first come into if
we're not prepared for it

00:15:04.160 --> 00:15:06.380 align:middle line:84%
because it also has
to do with a changing

00:15:06.380 --> 00:15:09.350 align:middle line:84%
of the sense of your
own individual identity

00:15:09.350 --> 00:15:10.550 align:middle line:90%
as a person.

00:15:10.550 --> 00:15:12.540 align:middle line:90%
Much of that tends to go away.

00:15:12.540 --> 00:15:14.030 align:middle line:90%
She was struggling.

00:15:14.030 --> 00:15:18.020 align:middle line:84%
She was struggling with how
do I live life in this state?

00:15:18.020 --> 00:15:20.000 align:middle line:84%
It turns out, she was
fortunate, she ended up

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:22.280 align:middle line:84%
having to go to a conference
shortly thereafter.

00:15:22.280 --> 00:15:26.330 align:middle line:84%
And at the conference, she
encountered a Buddhist monk.

00:15:26.330 --> 00:15:29.640 align:middle line:84%
And she asked the Buddhist
monk, can I speak with you?

00:15:29.640 --> 00:15:31.070 align:middle line:90%
I'm struggling with something.

00:15:31.070 --> 00:15:34.490 align:middle line:84%
He said yes, they sat down,
she explained her practice

00:15:34.490 --> 00:15:37.460 align:middle line:84%
and what happened and where
she was at that moment.

00:15:37.460 --> 00:15:41.820 align:middle line:84%
And he-- actually when
she shared that with him,

00:15:41.820 --> 00:15:44.630 align:middle line:84%
she just began to cry because
it had been such a load for her,

00:15:44.630 --> 00:15:46.940 align:middle line:90%
trying to decide what to do.

00:15:46.940 --> 00:15:50.030 align:middle line:84%
He was very thoughtful and he
said, what you're experiencing,

00:15:50.030 --> 00:15:54.010 align:middle line:84%
this is the normal trajectory
of spiritual development.

00:15:54.010 --> 00:15:56.060 align:middle line:90%
And you have a choice.

00:15:56.060 --> 00:16:00.540 align:middle line:84%
You can either go back and
accept the conditioned reality

00:16:00.540 --> 00:16:04.500 align:middle line:84%
that you've been living in
or stay on the path you're on

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:05.970 align:middle line:84%
and eventually it
will get easier,

00:16:05.970 --> 00:16:07.530 align:middle line:84%
it'll evolve, and
develop, and it'll

00:16:07.530 --> 00:16:09.630 align:middle line:84%
become more rich
of an experience

00:16:09.630 --> 00:16:11.850 align:middle line:84%
because the beginning
of these states,

00:16:11.850 --> 00:16:15.390 align:middle line:84%
can feel kind of isolated
even though it's essentially

00:16:15.390 --> 00:16:16.890 align:middle line:90%
a oneness state.

00:16:16.890 --> 00:16:18.687 align:middle line:84%
Of course, she's
progressed forward.

00:16:18.687 --> 00:16:20.520 align:middle line:84%
And there are many such
stories in the book.

00:16:20.520 --> 00:16:21.180 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:16:21.180 --> 00:16:22.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes, there are.

00:16:22.050 --> 00:16:24.330 align:middle line:84%
And what you bring
up is interesting

00:16:24.330 --> 00:16:26.850 align:middle line:84%
and what we're talking about
there are the notion of spirit

00:16:26.850 --> 00:16:30.910 align:middle line:84%
and mind and how one defines
the other, when in fact,

00:16:30.910 --> 00:16:35.100 align:middle line:84%
you can't even separate them
in the truest sense of the word

00:16:35.100 --> 00:16:38.880 align:middle line:84%
and certainly in hermetic
parlance and many others,

00:16:38.880 --> 00:16:41.160 align:middle line:90%
many traditions.

00:16:41.160 --> 00:16:45.390 align:middle line:84%
All there is-- that's
all there is, is mind

00:16:45.390 --> 00:16:47.430 align:middle line:84%
but that doesn't
mean left brain.

00:16:47.430 --> 00:16:51.150 align:middle line:84%
It means perception,
awareness, the ability

00:16:51.150 --> 00:16:53.940 align:middle line:90%
to articulate between themes.

00:16:53.940 --> 00:16:58.290 align:middle line:84%
And it's always seemed to me
that the biggest roadblock

00:16:58.290 --> 00:17:04.080 align:middle line:84%
for many people to having a
clear connection with higher

00:17:04.080 --> 00:17:04.880 align:middle line:90%
mind--

00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:09.510 align:middle line:84%
higher mind, which is
part of the soul complex

00:17:09.510 --> 00:17:11.780 align:middle line:90%
is sense of identity.

00:17:11.780 --> 00:17:14.869 align:middle line:84%
As much as we try-- we
try to protect the story

00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:18.109 align:middle line:84%
we've built about ourselves
and who we think we are,

00:17:18.109 --> 00:17:23.030 align:middle line:84%
and that really closes down the
ability to just flat blossom

00:17:23.030 --> 00:17:24.890 align:middle line:84%
and open to that
incredible connection

00:17:24.890 --> 00:17:27.859 align:middle line:84%
because you might find out
something new that you're not

00:17:27.859 --> 00:17:30.950 align:middle line:90%
or you are.

00:17:30.950 --> 00:17:35.210 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: We all tend to hold on
to our identity, this egotism.

00:17:35.210 --> 00:17:37.460 align:middle line:90%
And that keeps us stuck, yeah.

00:17:37.460 --> 00:17:39.530 align:middle line:84%
But when people get
on a spiritual path,

00:17:39.530 --> 00:17:41.720 align:middle line:84%
something happens and that
opening arises, and then

00:17:41.720 --> 00:17:42.650 align:middle line:90%
they're on their way.

00:17:42.650 --> 00:17:44.820 align:middle line:84%
And that's also much of
the story of the book.

00:17:44.820 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:84%
It's not only the story of
the individual scientist,

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:50.540 align:middle line:84%
it's what's happened to them and
how they got on their journey.

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:53.600 align:middle line:84%
But it's also about the
larger spiritual journey--

00:17:53.600 --> 00:17:55.400 align:middle line:84%
consciousness
development journey

00:17:55.400 --> 00:17:58.610 align:middle line:84%
that all human beings are
absolutely entitled to

00:17:58.610 --> 00:18:01.350 align:middle line:84%
and need to take
responsibility to start on

00:18:01.350 --> 00:18:02.990 align:middle line:90%
if they're not already on it.

00:18:02.990 --> 00:18:04.940 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, and
need to develop.

00:18:04.940 --> 00:18:08.000 align:middle line:84%
And this is the part I think
that's really tough for people,

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:11.900 align:middle line:84%
is to develop the faith that
life with the capital L,

00:18:11.900 --> 00:18:15.140 align:middle line:84%
meaning you, your soul,
your guidance, everything,

00:18:15.140 --> 00:18:19.620 align:middle line:84%
is all there to lift you,
not to work against you.

00:18:19.620 --> 00:18:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And so having that faith
to understand change is OK.

00:18:23.300 --> 00:18:26.270 align:middle line:84%
Seeing yourself differently
and others differently is OK.

00:18:26.270 --> 00:18:27.900 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Yeah, absolutely.

00:18:27.900 --> 00:18:28.700 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:28.700 --> 00:18:33.710 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: And if science was
in that corner, so to speak,

00:18:33.710 --> 00:18:38.000 align:middle line:84%
providing that information,
just philosophically number one,

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:42.920 align:middle line:84%
or if some of the billions of
a year that go to biomedical

00:18:42.920 --> 00:18:46.130 align:middle line:84%
and all kinds of science
research were devoted to that

00:18:46.130 --> 00:18:49.760 align:middle line:84%
so we as human beings can really
begin to understand and are

00:18:49.760 --> 00:18:51.152 align:middle line:90%
supported in our potential--

00:18:51.152 --> 00:18:52.610 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --beautiful
it would be.

00:18:52.610 --> 00:18:53.943 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: It would be beautiful.

00:18:53.943 --> 00:18:56.360 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Our reality
would be beautiful.

00:18:56.360 --> 00:18:59.628 align:middle line:84%
And it's just-- it's
not that far away.

00:18:59.628 --> 00:19:00.920 align:middle line:90%
And I think we're headed there.

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:01.910 align:middle line:90%
We talked about that.

00:19:01.910 --> 00:19:04.490 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about Dean
Radin for a moment.

00:19:04.490 --> 00:19:06.220 align:middle line:84%
A lot of our viewers
know Dean and you

00:19:06.220 --> 00:19:07.820 align:middle line:90%
know Dean and I've met Dean.

00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:09.770 align:middle line:84%
I've been in his
workshops where we're

00:19:09.770 --> 00:19:15.170 align:middle line:84%
talking about utilizing the
mind beyond time and space

00:19:15.170 --> 00:19:18.260 align:middle line:84%
and his feelings on this,
because he's really, I mean,

00:19:18.260 --> 00:19:20.790 align:middle line:84%
he's known for
his rational ways.

00:19:20.790 --> 00:19:23.000 align:middle line:84%
But on the other
hand, the experiments

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:26.690 align:middle line:84%
he's conducted and
overseen are really--

00:19:26.690 --> 00:19:30.300 align:middle line:84%
you can't argue the
results anymore.

00:19:30.300 --> 00:19:31.160 align:middle line:90%
We can't.

00:19:31.160 --> 00:19:33.170 align:middle line:84%
Tell us about his
position on the world

00:19:33.170 --> 00:19:34.320 align:middle line:90%
of scientific materialism.

00:19:34.320 --> 00:19:35.120 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Yeah.

00:19:35.120 --> 00:19:37.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, he's not in
favor of it, of course,

00:19:37.490 --> 00:19:39.620 align:middle line:90%
and he's been such a pioneer.

00:19:39.620 --> 00:19:42.560 align:middle line:84%
Probably the leading edge,
so to speak, of science

00:19:42.560 --> 00:19:46.282 align:middle line:84%
is to have the most rigorous
scientific methodology, which

00:19:46.282 --> 00:19:48.740 align:middle line:84%
is always admired, of course,
and needed if you want to get

00:19:48.740 --> 00:19:51.120 align:middle line:90%
into journals and so forth.

00:19:51.120 --> 00:19:52.730 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of that
has been driven

00:19:52.730 --> 00:19:54.320 align:middle line:90%
by his own personal experience.

00:19:54.320 --> 00:19:57.800 align:middle line:84%
And he shared with me when
we interviewed for the book.

00:19:57.800 --> 00:20:01.220 align:middle line:84%
And this was an experience he
had when he was in college.

00:20:01.220 --> 00:20:03.740 align:middle line:84%
And it turned out
it was his birthday,

00:20:03.740 --> 00:20:07.063 align:middle line:84%
but he had been
born on a leap year.

00:20:07.063 --> 00:20:08.480 align:middle line:84%
And he's walking
across the campus

00:20:08.480 --> 00:20:11.180 align:middle line:84%
and he was thinking himself,
oh, today is my birthday.

00:20:11.180 --> 00:20:14.210 align:middle line:84%
And what happened is he
shifted his consciousness,

00:20:14.210 --> 00:20:17.330 align:middle line:84%
spontaneously
shifted, and suddenly

00:20:17.330 --> 00:20:20.120 align:middle line:84%
he stepped into a new
dimension, so to speak.

00:20:20.120 --> 00:20:22.700 align:middle line:84%
And after he came into
the new dimension,

00:20:22.700 --> 00:20:25.220 align:middle line:90%
he calls these step functions.

00:20:25.220 --> 00:20:27.650 align:middle line:84%
And he's had several of
them in his life since then.

00:20:27.650 --> 00:20:30.560 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And how does
he define step function?

00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:33.680 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: It's when you leave
a prior state of consciousness

00:20:33.680 --> 00:20:35.790 align:middle line:90%
behind, and you're in a new one.

00:20:35.790 --> 00:20:38.600 align:middle line:84%
And when he stepped
into the step function

00:20:38.600 --> 00:20:40.910 align:middle line:84%
on the college
campus, he looked back

00:20:40.910 --> 00:20:42.770 align:middle line:84%
in his memory of his
prior life and he said,

00:20:42.770 --> 00:20:46.460 align:middle line:84%
it was like I had been
living in a fog, in a dream,

00:20:46.460 --> 00:20:48.320 align:middle line:90%
my whole life up to that point.

00:20:48.320 --> 00:20:50.450 align:middle line:84%
And then going forward,
it was no more fog,

00:20:50.450 --> 00:20:53.750 align:middle line:84%
there was no more dream, it
was utter lucidity about who

00:20:53.750 --> 00:20:55.970 align:middle line:84%
he was, the nature
of consciousness,

00:20:55.970 --> 00:20:59.000 align:middle line:84%
mind consciousness, as
let's say mind existing

00:20:59.000 --> 00:21:02.690 align:middle line:84%
within consciousness because
consciousness is everything.

00:21:02.690 --> 00:21:05.510 align:middle line:84%
And that began to
direct his future work,

00:21:05.510 --> 00:21:09.630 align:middle line:84%
ultimately become a scientist
and to guide the work he does.

00:21:09.630 --> 00:21:10.430 align:middle line:90%
It's beautiful.

00:21:10.430 --> 00:21:11.230 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It is.

00:21:11.230 --> 00:21:12.410 align:middle line:90%
And he says you can't--

00:21:12.410 --> 00:21:15.020 align:middle line:84%
we shouldn't just throw
out scientific materialism

00:21:15.020 --> 00:21:18.230 align:middle line:84%
because it's very useful in
proving a lot in this world,

00:21:18.230 --> 00:21:20.900 align:middle line:84%
but we cannot limit
ourselves to it any longer.

00:21:20.900 --> 00:21:23.640 align:middle line:84%
We're doing ourselves a
disservice as a species now.

00:21:23.640 --> 00:21:24.440 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Totally.

00:21:24.440 --> 00:21:26.630 align:middle line:84%
There's so much to
be said about that.

00:21:26.630 --> 00:21:30.860 align:middle line:84%
The materialism side and then
there's this term "scientism."

00:21:30.860 --> 00:21:33.650 align:middle line:84%
Leon Kass, he was the chair
of Bioethics Committee

00:21:33.650 --> 00:21:36.290 align:middle line:84%
for the president's counsel
at the White House some years

00:21:36.290 --> 00:21:38.420 align:middle line:84%
back, and he spoke
about scientism

00:21:38.420 --> 00:21:39.700 align:middle line:90%
as does Rupert Sheldrake.

00:21:39.700 --> 00:21:40.700 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, he does.

00:21:40.700 --> 00:21:43.760 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: Scientism is basically
this idea that science,

00:21:43.760 --> 00:21:47.360 align:middle line:84%
as we know it, has become a kind
of religion for many people.

00:21:47.360 --> 00:21:50.540 align:middle line:84%
And Kass says it's basically
a soulless scientism,

00:21:50.540 --> 00:21:54.980 align:middle line:84%
and has been draining from
us, as people, mystery,

00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:56.300 align:middle line:90%
the mystery of our existence.

00:21:56.300 --> 00:21:58.940 align:middle line:84%
It's trying to just
quantify everything

00:21:58.940 --> 00:22:02.930 align:middle line:84%
as a manifestation of
the material world only.

00:22:02.930 --> 00:22:06.140 align:middle line:84%
Sheldrake speaks of the
scientific priesthood.

00:22:06.140 --> 00:22:08.960 align:middle line:90%
And that's all that has to go.

00:22:08.960 --> 00:22:09.963 align:middle line:90%
It absolutely must go.

00:22:09.963 --> 00:22:10.880 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It must go.

00:22:10.880 --> 00:22:14.300 align:middle line:84%
>> MILLS: So that we can emerge
into our own and let science

00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:17.000 align:middle line:84%
emerge into what
it was, was to be.

00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:19.190 align:middle line:84%
And I write in the book
about that initial split

00:22:19.190 --> 00:22:21.110 align:middle line:90%
back four centuries ago.

00:22:21.110 --> 00:22:24.500 align:middle line:84%
Science should have been by
our side all these centuries,

00:22:24.500 --> 00:22:27.830 align:middle line:84%
supporting us, guiding
us to flowering

00:22:27.830 --> 00:22:29.870 align:middle line:90%
into who we were to be.

00:22:29.870 --> 00:22:32.360 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, up to this vision
of the future of the Earth,

00:22:32.360 --> 00:22:35.810 align:middle line:84%
manifesting love and that
becoming a primary experience

00:22:35.810 --> 00:22:36.680 align:middle line:90%
for human beings.

00:22:36.680 --> 00:22:38.690 align:middle line:84%
But it's been mainly
an impediment,

00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:40.400 align:middle line:90%
but it's not too late.

00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:41.400 align:middle line:90%
It can evolve.

00:22:41.400 --> 00:22:42.200 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:22:42.200 --> 00:22:45.140 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, Richard Feynman,
you wrote about in the book

00:22:45.140 --> 00:22:48.290 align:middle line:84%
as well, Nobel Prize winner
in physics, physicists are--

00:22:48.290 --> 00:22:50.930 align:middle line:84%
it's a little easier, it seems,
for physicists to get out

00:22:50.930 --> 00:22:51.410 align:middle line:90%
there--

00:22:51.410 --> 00:22:51.770 align:middle line:90%
>> MILLS: Agreed.

00:22:51.770 --> 00:22:53.120 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --because
they're already working kind

00:22:53.120 --> 00:22:54.680 align:middle line:90%
of in a non-physical world.

00:22:54.680 --> 00:22:57.380 align:middle line:84%
So scientific materialism
doesn't always--

00:22:57.380 --> 00:22:59.630 align:middle line:84%
doesn't apply to physicists
