00:24:22.600 --> 00:24:24.490 align:middle line:84%
And I think I started
with Michael Talbot,

00:24:24.490 --> 00:24:27.350 align:middle line:84%
"Beyond the Quantum," I
think that was my first book.

00:24:27.350 --> 00:24:30.880 align:middle line:84%
And I still remember how
I felt when I read it,

00:24:30.880 --> 00:24:34.450 align:middle line:84%
and it is mind-boggling
to, I think,

00:24:34.450 --> 00:24:36.790 align:middle line:84%
almost everyone,
including the physicists,

00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:39.700 align:middle line:84%
to think we're sitting
here talking to each other

00:24:39.700 --> 00:24:41.710 align:middle line:84%
and we have a cup
of tea and a table

00:24:41.710 --> 00:24:44.080 align:middle line:84%
but there's actually
nothing here.

